description:
What: Add four new dispatch cases to relay/src/ws.rs read loop: sealed_broadcast, sealed_whisper, publish_hpke_key, get_hpke_key. Relay treats sealed bytes as fully opaque — never deserializes them.

Algorithm:
1. Read /home/mark/WORK/nie/relay/src/ws.rs and /home/mark/WORK/nie/relay/src/store.rs
2. Add imports at top of ws.rs: SealedBroadcastParams, SealedDeliverParams, SealedWhisperParams, SealedWhisperDeliverParams, PublishHpkeKeyParams, GetHpkeKeyParams, GetHpkeKeyResult, and new rpc_methods constants
3. In match req.method.as_str() block, add AFTER the existing BROADCAST arm:

   rpc_methods::SEALED_BROADCAST => {
     let params: SealedBroadcastParams = deserialize or send_client_error + continue;
     if require_subscription && !is_subscribed { send_client_error + continue; }
     let message_id = Uuid::new_v4().to_string();
     // SECURITY: sealed bytes are opaque — relay must never unwrap them
     let deliver = JsonRpcNotification::new(rpc_methods::SEALED_DELIVER, SealedDeliverParams { sealed: params.sealed });
     let deliver_json = serde_json::to_string(&deliver).unwrap(); // derived Serialize, cannot fail
     state.broadcast(Some(&pub_id.0), deliver_json).await;
     let ack = JsonRpcResponse::success(req.id, BroadcastResult { message_id }).unwrap();
     client_tx.send(serde_json::to_string(&ack).unwrap()).await.ok();
   }

4. Add SEALED_WHISPER arm (after WHISPER):
   - Parse SealedWhisperParams { to, sealed }
   - Validate to != pub_id.0 (no self-whisper)
   - Forward as SealedWhisperDeliverParams { to: to.clone(), sealed } to state.deliver_live(&to, ...)
   - Send OkResult back to sender

5. Add PUBLISH_HPKE_KEY arm (after PUBLISH_KEY_PACKAGE):
   - Parse PublishHpkeKeyParams { public_key }
   - Validate public_key.len() == 32 (X25519 key must be exactly 32 bytes)
   - store.save_hpke_key(&pub_id.0, &public_key)?  // persist to DB
   - Send OkResult back to sender
   - No broadcast needed (peers fetch on demand via GET_HPKE_KEY)

6. Add GET_HPKE_KEY arm (after GET_KEY_PACKAGE):
   - Parse GetHpkeKeyParams { pub_id: target }
   - let key_data = store.get_hpke_key(&target)?  // Ok(None) if not published yet
   - Send GetHpkeKeyResult { pub_id: target, public_key: key_data }
   - No authentication required for this lookup (same as GET_KEY_PACKAGE)

7. Run cargo check -p nie-relay; cargo test -p nie-relay

Defensive programming rules:
- SEALED_BROADCAST handler must NOT inspect params.sealed — opaque bytes only (CLAUDE.md §3)
- SEALED_WHISPER must NOT add a from field to SealedWhisperDeliverParams — doing so would expose sender
- Relay NEVER calls any HPKE function — it only stores/forwards the sealed bytes
- public_key.len() != 32 must return invalid_params error before any DB write
- GET_HPKE_KEY is unauthenticated: any authenticated client can query any pub_id (like GET_KEY_PACKAGE)
- serde_json::to_string on derived Serialize cannot fail — unwrap() is intentional (document with comment per CLAUDE.md §11)
- store errors must bubble up; use ? with map_err to RelayError or log + continue
